285 g Shrimp
¾ cup Basmati Rice
113 g Baby Spinach
113 g Baby Tomatoes
7 g Dill
1 unit(s) Lemon
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 tbsp Vegetable Stock Powder
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
28 g Almonds, sliced
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
½ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add rice, vegetable stock powder, half the Zesty Garlic spice blend, and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter to boiling water. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, zest, then juice lemon.
Thinly slice cucumber.
Halve tomatoes.
Roughly chop half the spinach. (The whole spinach will be for your salad.)
Roughly chop dill.

Combine remaining Zesty Garlic Blend and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil in a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
Using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp. Pat dry with paper towels. Add to bowl with and toss to coat. Arrange on a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Roast in the bottom of the oven until cooked through, 8-10 min.**

Add feta, lemon zest, mayo and half the dill to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) lemon juice, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Fluff rice with a fork. Stir in chopped spinach. Cover and let stand until spinach wilts,1-2 min.

Add cucumber, tomatoes, almonds and remaining spinach to bowl with dressing. Toss to coat.
Divide rice, shrimp and salad between plates.
Dollop feta-dill sauce over top.
Sprinkle remaining dill over top, if desired.

If you've opted to get shrimp, using a strainer drain and rinse shrimp. Pat dry with paper towels. Transfer to a medium bowl, add Zesty Garlic oil mix and toss to coat. Arrange on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Cook in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the tilapia.**